Today I shared with @Florida_Today some critical post-Apollo 11 quarantine lessons that still apply today in dealing with the #coronavirus. For now, let’s say we take one small step to produce another giant leap for America.

Well done @SpaceX on successfully launching another batch of 60 Starlink Satellites into orbit! Yesterday's launch marks the 84th Falcon 9 flight, making your dynamo rocket the most flown U.S. rocket in use today. Keep up the great work!

#OTD in 1972 Apollo 16 astronauts Charlie Duke and John Young landed Lunar Module (LM) Orion on the Moon in the Lunar Highlands (Descartes Highlands). Both men became the ninth and tenth people to walk on the lunar surface.

Whether it’s in our backyard or in space, technology helps us explore the world around us. In #NASAatHome's newest activity, find out how space technology protects our national parks and our outdoor explorers: https://go.nasa.gov/3al5PAm #EarthDayWeek

One of America's greatest strengths is our ability to work together to solve any challenge that comes our way. @NASA joined forces with industry and local gov'ts in CA to build medical devices to help #COVID19 patients. Learn more about their efforts:
Did you catch this space history clue on @Jeopardy this past week? Who knows the "question" about my buddies?

Take 50% off ALL #Apollo11 shirts today & add some SPACE to your self-quarantine wardrobe. If you're like me, comfort has become a priority during this home-time, and these shirts offer the ultimate, "comfy self-quarantine attire". Get yours http://roadtoapollo50th.com/apparel/ Code: Comfy
This indeed will be a site to behold. @NASA #LaunchAmerica

#OTD 50 years ago – @NASA successfully brought the #Apollo13 crew home. Many coined their rescue operation as @NASA's finest hour. Without the hard work and ingenuity of Gene Kranz and the Mission Control team, the "successful failure" would not have been achieved.

I'm working remotely too by autographing prints of the #Apollo11 crew at the start of our 3-week quarantine, talking with Pres. Nixon after our lunar landing. Proceeds benefit the @SalvationArmyUS #COVID19 recovery efforts. Go to http://apollospaceshop.com #BuzzAldrinForStayingSaf https://twitter.com/Firouz_Naderi/status/1250117957373456385

#OTD in 1912, Harriet Quimby became the first woman to fly solo across the English Channel. She was also the first American woman to earn a pilot's license. To this day, she remains one of the most popular pioneer female aviators ever.

#OTD in 1972, #Apollo16 launched from Cape Canaveral on its 238,000-mile journey to the Moon. This mission would be the second-to-last to land on the lunar surface and the second to land in the lunar highlands. Their efforts to advance our space program will never be forgotten.
